Titanic Data Dashboard (Looker Studio Project)
Objective

Analyze passenger data to understand:

Survival rate

Gender survival comparison

Passenger class distribution

Age group survival

Fare distribution

Step 1: Prepare Titanic Dataset

Create a Google Sheet with sample columns like this:

PassengerId	Survived	Pclass	Name	Sex	Age	Fare	Embarked
1	0	3	Allen	male	22	7.25	S
2	1	1	Cumings	female	38	71.28	C
3	1	3	Heikkinen	female	26	7.92	S
4	1	1	Futrelle	female	35	53.10	S
5	0	3	Allen	male	35	8.05	S

Important fields:

Survived (0 = No, 1 = Yes)
Pclass (1,2,3)
Sex
Age
Fare
Embarked

Upload to Google Sheets.

Step 2: Open Looker Studio

Open lookerstudio.google.com

Click Create

Select Report

Step 3: Connect Dataset

Steps:

Click Add Data

Choose Google Sheets

Select Titanic spreadsheet

Select worksheet

Click Add to Report

Step 4: Verify Data Types

Left panel → Data fields

Ensure correct types:

Field	Type
PassengerId	Number
Survived	Number
Pclass	Number
Sex	Text
Age	Number
Fare	Number
Embarked	Text
Step 5: Create Calculated Fields

Go to:

Resource → Manage added data source → Edit → Add Field

Survival Status
CASE
WHEN Survived = 1 THEN "Survived"
ELSE "Not Survived"
END

Name:

Survival Status
Passenger Class Label
CASE
WHEN Pclass = 1 THEN "First Class"
WHEN Pclass = 2 THEN "Second Class"
ELSE "Third Class"
END
